# e2e-flight — one-Task implementation worker (Cursor runtime)

When the user invokes e2e-flight ("e2e-flight", "/e2e-flight", "flight", "drain the queue", "run the flight loop", "implement the selected tasks"), follow the flow defined in [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) → `.agents/skills/e2e-flight/SKILL.md`.

**Cursor runtime constraints:**

- Cursor has no parallel worktree fan-out (`spawn_agents_on_csv` unavailable). Step 0 capability probe routes to **Codex serial branch mode**: one slice at a time, orchestrator switches to `slice/<story-id>` branch, worker commits, orchestrator merges back.
- If agent spawn (`spawn_agent`) is fully unavailable, Step 0 emits `<e2e-stall reason="fanout-unavailable" />` and exits — never falls back to inline slice work.
- Slices run SEQUENTIALLY in `depends_on` order. No ready-set parallel dispatch.

For full-fidelity parallel execution, the Claude Code skill version is available: `npx e2e-engineering init --target claude`.
